select_highlighted(25.10)                            select_highlighted(25.10)

Name
       select_highlighted - Selects highlighted objects

Syntax
       select_highlighted

       [-help]

       [-type <string>]

       Selects highlighted objects. If -type is specified, selects highlighted
       objects of the specified type.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each select_highlighted parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man select_highlighted

       -type <string>
              Specifies  the  type  of the highlighted objects to be selected.
              Options are instance, wire, and via.

Examples
              * The following command selects all highlighted instances.

                select_highlighted -type instance

Related Information
              * gui_select

              * highlight

